/*

THE COMIPLER CAN'T BE ABLE TO CONVERT THE STATEMENT DUE TO GRAMMATICAL MISTAKE
SEMICOLON DETECTED 
SYNTHETICAL ERROR --> ERROR IN GRAMMAR OR IN RULES
SEMANTICAL ERROR --> ERROR IN LOGIC AND MEANING

EXCEPTIONS:-
THE PROGRAMM OR STATEMENT IS SYN. CORRECT BUT SOME LOGIC IS MISSING THEN IT LEADS TO ABNORMAL TERMINATIONOF YOUR APPLICATION 

CHECKED EXCEPTION AND UNCHECKED EXCEPTION
MUST BE DECLARED BY USING (THROWS)
IN CPP ALL THE EXCEPTION ARE NOT DEFINED
IT IS PROGRAMMER REQUEIREMENT TO CATCH THE EXCEPTIONS 

TYPES OF EXCEPTION IN CPP
1. STL EXCEPTION(PREDEFINED EXCEPTION) which is throw by the compiler at run time 
    ->std:: runtime_error
    ->std:: logic error
    
2. USER DEFINED EXCEPTION
3. BUILT IN ERRORS 

IF YOU DEFINE TRY BLOCK CATCH BLOCK IS MANDATORY


WHENEVER WE WANT TO THROW AN EXCEPTION WE CAN THROW BY THROW KEYWORD WITH EXCEPTION CLASS THEN THE CATCH BLOCK CATCH THAT EXCEPTION BY CLASS OBJECT OR PARTICULAR CLASS OBJECT AND WE CAN DISPLAY ERROR THORW BY CLASS OBJECT IN CATCH BLOCK EXAMPLE e.what()
WHEH  WE ARE TRYING TO OVERWRTIE A METHOD WHAT DERIVED CLASS TO THE BASE CLASS HAVE A RESTICTION TO OVERWRITE BY PARTICLAUR MTHOD NO() EXCEPT SPACE OVERWRITE

*/